1.Download and Install the NodeJS.

    Website : https://nodejs.org/en/download/

    file name : node-v6.10.2-x64.msi


2. Download and Install the GIT.

    Website : https://git-scm.com/downloads

    file name : Git-2.12.2.2-64-bit.exe


3. Register with GitHub.

    Website : https://github.com/join


4. Download the IDE (WebStrom)

    Website : https://www.jetbrains.com/webstorm/download/#section=windows

    file name : WebStrom-2017.1.1.exe


5. Add the Bower plugin to WebStrom IDE.

    - Open the Integrated Terminal in WebStrom IDE.

        (Alt + F12)

    - Execute the Following NodeJS Command

      >npm install -g bower


6. Download and Install the MongoDB.

    WebSite : https://www.mongodb.com/download-center#community

    file name : mongodb-win32-x86_64-2008plus-ssl-3.4.3-signed.exe


    - Create the Following Folder Structure in "C Drive" After Successful Installation Of MongoDB

    C:\data\db


7. Download and Install the Rest Client (Postman)

    Website : https://app.getpostman.com/app/download/win64

    file name : Postman-win64-4.10.7-Setup.exe


8. Checkout the Code From the Following URL.

    https://github.com/ajsnaresh/AJS_Classes.git





















